# AEP Rules for Cursor

This file defines how Cursor should interact with AEP projects.

## Project Structure

When working in an AEP project, follow this structure:

```
KERNEL/
  STATE.md      # Current state
  PROGRAM.md    # Execution flow
  BOOT.md       # Boot sequence
  ISA.md        # Instruction set

RESOURCES/
  *.md          # Resource files

AEP/
  AEP-*.md      # Protocol specifications
```

## Resource Format

All resources must follow this format:

```yaml
---
type: project|status|skill|adr|incident|rule|template
id: unique-id
version: X.Y.Z
depends: [dep1, dep2]
status: draft|review|active|deprecated|archived
---
# Content here
```

## State Registers

State is maintained in R0-R7:

- R0: Session ID
- R1: Last action
- R2: Next action
- R3: Modified files (delta only)
- R4: Blockers
- R5: Active skill
- R6: Health (OK/FAIL)
- R7: Timestamp

## Rules

1. Never modify KERNEL/ files directly
2. Always validate resources before use
3. Keep R3 as delta only (no history)
4. Use Git for history, not state